history.content:
I took it for my math degree - it's definitely a "CS-y" math class, but unless you're super into like the specific numerical techniques machines use to do computations (aka a bunch of approximation techniques), I wouldn't particularly recommend it. IMO there are a bunch of more interesting CS classes, even if you're into math (think optimization, ML type classes).

That's just me though - I know a bunch of people that thought it was interesting.

I am figuring out what CS tech elective to take for next semester.

Has anyone taken Math128A? What did you think of the class?
history.subject: Math128A
